# squads — working with the `sq` CLI

<!-- squads:managed — regenerated by `sq sync`; do not edit by hand. -->
<!-- squads:version:{{ version }} -->

This project is managed by **squads**. Work is tracked as identified markdown items under
`{{ squad_dir }}/`, indexed in `{{ squad_dir }}/.squads.json`. Every item has a stable ID like
`TASK-000003` (the prefix marks the type; the number is globally unique).

## Golden rules

- The `.md` frontmatter is the source of truth; `sq` keeps the index in sync. Do not hand-edit
  frontmatter or the `<!-- sq:* -->` marker lines.
- Write prose (descriptions, user stories, findings) **directly** in the file body, between the
  markers. Use `sq` only for structural ops: create, status, comment, link.
- Reference related items by ID so others read the right context.

{% include "workflow.md.j2" %}

## Common commands

```bash
sq create task "Title" [--parent FEAT-000002] [--desc "..."]   # also: epic|feature|bug|decision|review|guide
sq status TASK-000003 InProgress                                # transition (validated per type)
sq show TASK-000003                                             # details
sq list --type task --status InProgress                         # filtered table
sq tree                                                         # hierarchy
sq link TASK-000003 --parent FEAT-000002                        # parent/child (validated)
```

Run `sq --help` (or `sq <command> --help`) for the full surface.
